{"id":1105,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":1105,"title":"Shechem","subtitle":"","short_title":"Shechem","uri":"/scriptures/bd/shechem","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/shechem.t1","order":".000.3636"},[".title","Shechem"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/shechem.p1","order":".000.3637"},["i","Shoulder."],"The most ancient of the sacred towns of the children of Israel, situated in a beautiful plain among the mountains of Ephraim, close to the two hills Ebal and Gerizim. It was visited by Abram on his first arrival in the promised land (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/12.6"},"Gen. 12:6"],"); Jacob bought land here (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/33.18-19"},"33:18–19"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/35.4"},"Gen. 35:4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/37.14"},"37:14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/7.16"},"Acts 7:16"],"). It was later included in the territory of Ephraim (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/17.7"},"Josh. 17:7"],") and became a Levitical city and a city of refuge (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/20.7"},"20:7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/21.21"},"21:21"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/6.67"},"1 Chr. 6:67"],"). Here Joshua addressed the people (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/24.1"},"Josh. 24:1"],"), and the bones of Joseph were buried (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/24.32"},"24:32"],"). Here Rehoboam came to be crowned in the hope of conciliating the northern tribes (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/12.1"},"1 Kgs. 12:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/10.1"},"2 Chr. 10:1"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/8.31"},"Judg. 8:31"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/9.6,46"},"9:6, 46"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/21.19"},"21:19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/12.25"},"1 Kgs. 12:25"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/7.28"},"1 Chr. 7:28"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ps/60.6"},"Ps. 60:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/41.5"},"Jer. 41:5"],"). The modern town of Nablus lies near the ancient site of Shechem."]]],"refs":null}
